Backed By Three Generations Of Experience IN The Propane Industry, Gastec Has Incorporated 60 Years Of Proven Methods Into Its Operations. We Currently Service Thousands Of Customers--Both Residential And Commercial--With A Friendly, Professional Approach And Exceptional Product. Company Description: Gc Electric Co. Inc. Was Started IN 1959 By Harold K. Gross And Russell Cunningham. IN 1961, Mr. Cunningham Sold His Share Of The Business To Harold Gross, Who Was The Sole Shareholder Of The Company For 35 Years, Until He Relinquished Much Of His Duties To His Son, Michael.Michael Gross Was President Of G-C Electric Co. Inc. For Over 20 Years And Carried The Company Into The New Millennium. David Cope Became Vice President Of Gc Electric On March 7, 2006. David Cope Became President Of Gc Electric IN 2016, And Michael Gross Is Currently Vice President & Ceo Of Gc Electric Co., Inc.Our Allentown Electric Company Has Grown To Include More Than 60 Employees. We Strive To Grow Our Business While Keeping True To Our Values As A Family- Owned Business, And Project A 40% Growth Over The Next 10 Years. We Have Since Expanded Our Services To Throughout The Lehigh Valley, Including Whitehall, Macungie, Coopersburg, And Catasauqua PA Areas.

Company Description: Established IN 1967, Gharda Chemicals Limited Is A Research-Based Company And A Pioneer IN Agrochemicals, Intermediates And Veterinary Drugs IN India. Its Various Agrochemicals Include Insecticides, Pesticides, Fungicides And Plant Growth Regulators. The Firm Generates Annual Sales Of Over $1 Trillion, Including Exports Of More Than $86 Billion. Its Dombivli And Lote Plants Are Iso 9001-2000, Iso 14001-2004 And Ohsas 18001-1999 Certified. The Company Received The Chemexcil Trishul Award For Outstanding Exports Among Large-Scale Chemical Manufacturers IN 1995 And 1996. It Is Also A Recipient Of The Indian Ministry Of Power S 2004 National Energy Conservation Award. Gharda Chemicals Limited Is The Only Indian Company To Receive The U.S. Registration (The Environmental Protection Agency Approval) For The Sale Of Chlorpyrifos Insecticide And Dicamba Herbicide IN The United States.

It Encompasses 200 Miles Of Waterways, Studded With Freight Terminals And Potential Plant Sites. It Is Located At The Intersection Of Three Major Rivers IN A Port That Receives Goods By Barge, Adds Manufacturing Value, And Markets The Resulting Products Throughout The World Through Efficient Distribution Networks.

Company Description: Hydro Carbide Plants Are Leading Suppliers Of Preformed Tungsten Carbide Compositions For Multiple Markets. The Company S Products Include Tungsten Carbide Rod, Die Parts, Rolls And Related Products For The Metalworking Market. Fansteel Hydro Carbide Is Also A Major Supplier Of Nozzles, Studs And Substrates, Valve Parts, Bearings And Other Wear Parts For The Oil And Energy Industries. Additional Industries Served Include Polycrystalline Diamond Production, Can-Making And Fluid Handling. At The 33,000-Square-Foot Gulfport, Miss., Facility, Products Are Mechanically Pressed By Specially Designed Equipment, Machined, Sintered And/OR Sinter/Hzp And Diamond-Wheel Ground For Exact Size And Geometry. Company Description: The History Of J.S. Vila CO, Inc IN 1884, Joseph Sabau Vila, An Immigrant From Spain, Founded J.S. Vila CO IN Philadelphia, Pennsylvania As A Regional Distributor Of Dyes And Chemicals To The Textile Industry. The Family Business Was Originally Located IN A Storefront Building On Front Street, And As The Business Grew, The Vila Family Moved Their Operation To Callowhill Street. Stanley Thachrah Purchased The Business From Joe Sala Vila, A Descendant Of Joseph Sabau, IN The 1950'S. He Continued To Expand The Business Until 1969, At Which Time, He Sold The Company To John C.H. Dempsey. John Brought 40 Years Of Related Experience From Ciba Geigy. He Eventually Incorporated The Business And Relocated It To The Frankford Section Of Philadelphia. His Son, John C. Dempsey, Later Partnered With His Father To Operate J.S. Vila Co. Inc Several Years Later, John C. Dempsey Iii, Grandson Of John C.H. Joined The Company. IN 1995, John C. Dempsey Iii Acquired The Company From His Father. John's Expertise IN The Industry Allowed Him To Expand Into Other Markets. J.S. Vila Continues To Specialize IN Dyes And Auxilary's For Textiles, While Also Being A Major National Distributor For The Dyes That Go Into Paints, Lubricants, Plastics, Adhesives, Car Care Products, Water And Tracers.

Company Description: We Are The 'energy Conservation Specialists.' Proudly Serving The Greater Pittsburgh Area Since 1977. For 40 Years Now, Mincin Insulation Has Been The Trusted Name IN Providing Affordable Comfort, Along With Superior Service, To Pittsburgh Residents. Our Mission Is To Help Our Community Conserve Energy. We Provide Installation Services That Includes Blown-IN Cellulose Insulation And Complimentary Air Sealing Materials Designed To Increase Comfort Throughout The Entirety Of Your Home. We Promote Healthy, Comfortable, And Sustainable Lifestyles To Our Customers.Mincin Insulation Specializes IN Installing Cellulose Insulation, Which Is A Superior Insulation Produced By Nature. All-Natural Wood Fibers Within The Product Provide Your Home With Maximum 'r-Value' Protection Against High Energy Costs And Cold, Drafty Walls. Green, Made From Recycled Newspapers, Is Treated For Pest Control And Is Fire Retardant. Cellulose Insulation When Installed Properly Makes A Great Insulator. We Dense Pack It IN The Walls And Open Blow It IN Attics. By Dense Packing IN Walls, There Is No Air Flow Unlike Fiberglass Products. Cellulose Also Makes A Great Sound Deaden-Er On Interior Walls. Insulating Your Home's Walls And Attic With Cellulose Will Reduce Your Winter Heating Bills And Summer Cooling Costs. Cellulose Is One Of The Few Products You Can Install IN Your Home That Will Actually Pay For Itself! We Employ Building Performance Institute 'bpi' Certified Individuals And Are Also Members Of The Well-Regarded Insulation Contractors Association Of America 'icaa' And Pennsylvania Builders Exchange ?pbx? Trade Associations.

Company Description: IN Today's Marketplace, It's Very Common To See Businesses Here Today And Gone Tomorrow. Here At Modern Gas Sales, Inc, We'Re Proud To Say That We Have Been IN The Propane Gas Industry For Over 50 Years Now. How Do We Remain A Leader IN Our Industry? By Providing Exceptional Service, Maintaining Low Prices, And Selling Only Top-Quality Heating Products. As A Family Owned And Operated Business We Transport Lp-Gas Directly From The Refinery To Our Valued Customers. This Enables US To Maintain A Competitive Price While At The Same Time Ensuring An Adequate Supply Of Propane. With The Recent Addition Of Our State-Of-The-Art Rail Terminal, We Are Able To Purchase Our Propane Supply At A Low Cost, Both Nationally And Internationally. Thus, We Pass Along The Savings To Our Valued Customers. Having Over A Million Gallons Of Storage Space IN Pennsylvania And New York We Can Ensure You Propane Anytime You Need. For Emergency Service We Are Available 24 Hours A Day, 7 Days A Week, 365 Days A Year. Our Number One Goal At Modern Gas Sales Is Customer Satisfaction. Without Customers We Wouldn't Be IN Existence. Our Door Is Always Open, Especially When It Comes To Servicing You Better.

Company Description: Founded IN 1875, Conocophillips Finds, Produces, Refines, Markets And Supplies Energy Resources To Individuals And Businesses Worldwide. The Company Operates Chevron Phillips Chemical Company, Which Produces A Range Of Olefins, Polyolefins, Aromatics And Styrenics, And Piping And Proprietary Plastics. Company Description: Established IN 1938, Moore Aviation Inc. Is One Of The Leading Aviation Flight Schools IN Western Pennsylvania. Also Provides Additional Training For Cfi (Certified Flight Instructor), Cfii (Instrument Instructor) And Mei (Multi-Engine Instructor). Moore Aviation, Inc. Is An Equal Opportunity Employer.

Company Description: Morgan Am&T Is One Of The Leading Providers Of Engineered Solutions. Morgan Am&T Is A Global Corporation With A Network Of Engineering And Production Facilities Located IN More Than 40 Countries Around The World. The Company Combines Vast Expertise And Capabilities With A Large Product Offering, Including A Range Of Carbon Graphite, Graphite, And Silicon Carbide. It Offers Design Assistance And High-Volume Production For Engineered Components Programs. The Carbon And Graphite Offered By Morgan Am&T Comprises Various Bearings, Seal Rings, Rotary Vane Compressors And Meters, High Temperature, Glass Handling And Continuous Casting. The Company Staffs Trained And Experienced Field Application Personnel And Research And Development And Test Facilities. It Offers A Wide Selection Of Tungsten Carbides And Tribological Materials To Simplify Engineered Component Procurement.

Company Description: New Pig Corporation Specializes IN Industrial Absorbents For Oil Spill Recovery Processes. It Offers Absorbent Pads And Mats, Oil Booms, Pillows, Pans, Shop Towels And Spill Containment Kits. The Company Also Provides Materials Handling, Spill Response, Stormwater Management, Workplace Safety And Facility Protection Products. New Pig Corporation Features 4-Drum Roll-Top Hardcovers And Pallets For Secondary Containment Purposes. Its Pig Repair Putty Serves Various Applications. The Company Also Supplies Products To Enhance Work Environments, Such As Roof Leak Repair Tools And Outdoor Ashtrays. New Pig Corporation Performs Barcoding And Labeling Services For Customers. The Company Was Founded IN 1985 And Is Based IN Tipton, Pa.

Company Description: Norquay Technology Was Founded IN 1987 With A Focus To Develop A Product Line And Custom Synthesis For Custom Proprietary Products. The Company S Specialty Is Low Volume Commercialization Of Specific Molecules For High-Performance Applications. It Utilizes Scale-Up And Process Optimization To Reduce Costs And Cycle Times While Understanding The Chemical Synthesis. Export Is An Important Growth Area For The Company, With Representatives For Specific Product Lines IN Europe, Asia, Central America And South America. The Company Manufactures Pharmaceutical, Photographic, Electronic, Polyolefin Metallocene Catalyst And Ultraviolet Stabilizer Product Lines. Specific Products Include Uv Stabilizers, Metallocene Single Site Catalysts, Phenyl Hydrazines, Indoles, High Performance Liquid Chromatography Grade Alkyl Sulfonates And High-Purity Compounds. Norquay Technology Is A Member Of The Synthetic Organic Chemical Manufacturers Association And Is Headquartered IN Chester, Pa.
